Title: Why Do We Still Pay For International Calls in 2025? |
Description: We live in an era where global communication is instant, continuous, and, thanks to apps like WhatsApp, Zoom and Messenger, usually completely free. Yes, technically the data is drawn down from your cellular data allowance, but free wi-fi is prevalent everywhere you work, shop or drink. Yet, if you, a typical New Zealand mobile user like me, pick up your phone and dial a family member in the UK, you will be hit with a retail charge that can be 50 to 100 times higher than the technical cost of routing that voice data, US$0.51/minute in my specific case. (I will use US$ as I have an international audience and everyone knows how to convert those)
